[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Subgroup Data Governance** | The demographic-and-attribute store (age, sex, race/ethnicity, language, insurance, ADI/SVI, dual-eligibility, SDOH attributes from PRAPARE/AHC HRSN/Z-codes) requires restricted read access distinct from the clinical-PHI access path; SDOH attributes may be governed differently under state law. CloudTrail data events enabled on all subgroup-data queries. QuickSight dashboards for fairness monitoring consume an aggregated subgroup-metrics table (alert rate by subgroup, calibration ECE by subgroup, intervention rate by subgroup, change in 30-day readmission rate per subgroup attributable to the program), not the raw demographic-joined worklist archive. IAM policies scope the fairness-analytics role to aggregated tables only; no role can join raw demographics to individual worklist rows outside the governance-approved subgroup-audit pipeline. |
