[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **AWS End User Messaging or a third-party SMS/IVR vendor for patient outreach.** The outreach itself (SMS check-ins, IVR calls) is often delivered through specialist healthcare communication vendors (CipherHealth, GetWellNetwork, Memora Health, Cipher). For SMS-only, AWS End User Messaging (formerly Pinpoint SMS and Voice) works. The integration boundary matters: keep PHI in HIPAA-eligible services; the patient-facing channel needs a BAA. TCPA compliance requires: pre-approved message templates by content category (PHI-bearing vs. de-identified), patient-consent capture as a structured event in the patient-state record at enrollment, immediate opt-out revocation handling, and audit trail in worklist-audit and intervention-audit indexes for TCPA defense. Template categories: appointment reminders (de-identified), symptom check-ins (PHI-bearing, requires express consent), and escalation notifications (de-identified, care-team-directed).
